[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Campina Grande banner.jpg"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Campina Grande"]}," is a city in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Paraíba"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Brazil"]]},". Second largest of its state, and the largest of the northeastern inlands (350 000 people), it has countrywide fame for midwinter parties, ",{"type":"''","value":["Festa Junina"]}," or ",{"type":"''","value":["São João"]},", in June. It also hosts a large out-of-season carnival, ",{"type":"''","value":["Micarande"]},", in April, and a few rodeos throughout the year.\n",{"type":"==","value":["Orientation"]},"\nThe city center lies on a hill along and around ",{"type":"''","value":["Avenida Marechal Floriano Peixito"]}," running east from the park ",{"type":"''","value":["Açude Velho"]}," with its obelisk known as ",{"type":"''","value":["Marco zero"]},". ",{"type":"''","value":["Praça da Bandeira"]}," is bull's eye. Five blocks south of the center is the ",{"type":"''","value":["Açude Novo"]},", a lake with some surrounding greenery.\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By Bus"]},"\nThe bus station, a blueprint of the one in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["João Pessoa"]]},", is on the SE outskirts of town, some 3 km from the centre. Take bus 500 or taxi (R$10) to the center.\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["João Pessoa"]]}," by ",{"type":"''","value":["Real Bus"]}," at least once an hour from 5AM-8PM, 2 hours, R$16."]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Sousa"]]}," by ",{"type":"''","value":["Guanabara"]},{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.expressoguanabara.com.br"]}," 6 daily, 5 hours, R$42."]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Juazeiro do Norte"]]}," by ",{"type":"''","value":["Guanabara"]},{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.expressoguanabara.com.br"]}]},{"type":"===","value":["By Plane"]},"\nThere is an airport with regional flights\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\nIf you stay in the centre, most is walkable.\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\nA few open air shacks around both ",{"type":"''","value":["Açude Velho"]}," and ",{"type":"''","value":["Açude Novo"]},".\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["drink"],["name=Bar Arte"],["url="],["email="],["address=Rua Treze de Maio, centre"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price=Entry R$3, small beer R$2,50."],["content=Live music several times a week. Can get crammed."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["drink"],["name=Saloon Bar"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions=Just west of Açude Velho"],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Live music and dancing on weekends."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["drink"],["name=Cachaçaria"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions=By Hiper Bompreço, near Açude Velho"],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Slightly upmarket bar-come-club"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\nDuring festival times prices can be as much as doubled, and posted prices might refer to these; always ask.\nA few hotels around the bus station, particularly newer ones of the fancier type.\nDowntown is a better option:\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Hotel Majestic"],["url=http:\/\/www.majestichotelpb.com"],["email="],["address=Rua Maciel Pinheiro 216, centre"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price=Double R$60"],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content=Great value. Neat, bright and clean. Wi-fi zone and internet in the reception. Air con and hot water showers. Good breakfast."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name